==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Technology
<hw>Tech*nol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ an art
+ <ets>-logy</ets>; cf. Gr. <?/ systematic treatment: cf. F.
<ets>technologie</ets>.]</ety> <def>Industrial science; the science of
systematic knowledge of the industrial arts, especially of the more
important manufactures, as spinning, weaving, metallurgy, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Technology</xex> is not an independent science,
having a set of doctrines of its own, but consists of applications of
the principles established in the various physical sciences (chemistry,
mechanics, mineralogy, etc.) to manufacturing processes.
<rj><au>Internat. Cyc.</au></rj> </note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Techy</ent>⟦br⟧
